# UnionOps — Platform Rules

## Product
Multi-union by design. Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/VISION.md` before any work.
Public brand: **UnionOps** (https://unionops.org). Slogan: **Solidarity.**
OPSEU/CAAT is reference tenant #1 (`seed/reference-tenant-opseu-caat.json`), not a code default.

## Current status
Phases **0–7 near-complete** (Postgres adapters flag-gated; default memory). Time **8b** + Calendar R0–R3 shipped. Next: Time 8c+ or COMMS_BACKLOG — see `.cursor/rules/roadmap-next.mdc` and `docs/audit/current-ground-truth.md`.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- Public comms: client-side tools; hub: Auth.js + API routes (memory default; Drizzle via `*_DB_BACKEND=postgres`)
- next-intl EN/FR with `[locale]` routing
- Zustand + `DataAdapter` (`LocalStorageAdapter` default; optional `ApiAdapter` for Hub Brand Kit / prefs)
- html-to-image, JSZip, jsPDF, Web Crypto (hybrid), ICS export; Zod on mutating Hub APIs

## Multi-Union Principles
1. No union names in core code — tenant config and seed data only
2. Every query scoped by `unionId`; RLS when Postgres lands
3. Modules opt-in per union (`enabledModules`)
4. CA/grievance steps from `CAConfig`, not hardcoded
5. Brand per-local via Brand Kit; `resolveLocalNumber()` returns 243 when empty
6. OPSEU/CAAT brand: `.cursor/rules/opseu-branding.mdc`

## Conventions
- `@/` imports; `"use client"` where needed
- Data via adapters only — never raw `localStorage`/`fetch` in tools
- Role-gate write UI to match API (`src/lib/qol/access.ts`, grievance/bumping access)
- i18n: both `messages/en.json` and `messages/fr.json`
- Commit at milestone end; update `docs/PROGRESS.md`
- Source-available (`LICENSE`); stewarded by Ryan Morris
- Privacy copy: Comms on-device; hosted Officer Hub ? operator is data controller
- Operator guides: `docs/guides/SETUP.md`, `docs/guides/DEPLOY.md`

## Testing
- `npm run test:unit` — Vitest
- `npm run test:smoke` — Playwright `@smoke` (includes hub login)
- axe-core a11y in smoke suite
- Before committing large / multi-file changes: run `npm run lint` and the relevant test suite(s); fix failures before push

## Do Not
- Cross-union data access
- Analytics or third-party tracking
- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`
- Skip MFA/audit for confidential modules
- Hardcode OPSEU/CAAT as default for new tenant signups
